# Ypsilanti Black Civil War monument

The Ypsilanti Black Civil War Monument was dedicated in June 2022, during a federal Juneteenth holiday by the city of Ypsilanti at Highland Cemetery, Michigan. The monument depicts three United States Colored soldiers and is meant to honor the state of Michigan's fallen colored troops and veterans who fought in the Civil War (1861â€“1865).
